15/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Public Order Minister Igli Toska said Wednesday (14 April) the government would establish a working group to co-ordinate security measures for the Summer Olympics in Athens. 
His comment followed a meeting with his Greek counterpart, Georgios Voulgarakis. 
They discussed joint efforts to provide increased border security during the Games, as well as intensified co-operation against international terrorism, trafficking and organised crime. 
(ATA, Albanian Radio - 14/04/04)
